File: A lab technician with the National Health Laboratory Services (NHLS) prepares a tent at a screening and testing drive in front of the Alexandra Madala Hostel in Johannesburg. JOHANNESBURG - There are 1,727 new COVID-19 cases in South Africa. This bring the total number of positive coronavirus cases to 30,967. There are now 32 more COVID-19 related deaths, bringing the total number to 643. WATCH: Mkhize briefing on alert level 3 According to the Health Department, a total of 701,883 tests have been conducted cumulatively of which 21,708 tests have been conducted since the last report. More than 16,116 people have recovered, resulting in more than 52-percent recovery. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.